RESULTS: The ratio of NAA/Cr in SCA3/MJD patients showed a significant reduction in the cerebellar cortex, dentatum, cerebellar vermis and medipeduncle (P{\textless}0.01) compared with the controls. The ratio of NAA/Cho also showed significant reduction in the dentatum and cerebellar vermis (P{\textless}0.01). A number of correlations were found between the metabolite ratios of (1)H-MRS and duration of the disease, age of onset, expanded CAG and SARA score in SCA3/MJD patients.
